The paper deals with the study of plane graphs and their properties, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of dilation and the classification of finite plane graphs of dilation 1 involve combinatorial and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The iterative procedure and the limit point set P* involve dynamical systems and chaos theory, which fall under the category of dynamical systems (cs.DS). The construction of a concrete point set Q and the gap theorem involve graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the study of the density of iterated crossing points and its relation to the dilation of finite plane graphs involves the analysis of algorithms and computational complexity, which fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
